claims:
3. An counterbalance system to accommodate an animal movements in a vertical plane:
comprising:
a. Preventing tension on a cable coupled to an animal's head when the animal moves down in a cage;
b. Preventing the cable from folding inside the cage when the animal moves up;
c. Pivoting the cable from a plate on a first end with a swivel centered above the cage; and
d. Counterbalancing the plate on a second end with weights slightly heavier than the cable to provide a continuous gentle upward pull on the animal's head.
